<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-91-0408 </DOCNO><TEXT>The article reviews the situation of gas supply and prices in North America.A continent-wide supply surplus, stemming from a combination of the 1979-1983contractual impasse, and an artificial shortage of transport capacitywill disappear only with truly open-access transportation and the resolutionof contractual disputes. The pivotal role played by the &quot;B-fuels&quot; markethas to be fully understood to determine the share of gas in the NorthAmerican industrial fuels mix and the profitability of gas productionand exploration. World oil prices are, therefore, the critical indexof future gas prices; they shouldn't, however, rise much higher in theplanning horizon.</TEXT></DOC>